6.3 Mechanics 

 



Page 15 of 29                                   
 

At launch, Decent.bet will offer multi-line slot machines consisting of 5 reels and up to 

5 lines. 

 

Bet sizes for each slot spin would be multiplied by the number of lines the player would 

like to play.  For example, if a user would like to spin with a bet size of 10 DBETs while 

playing 5 lines, the user would have to bet 50 DBETs while increasing chances of a 

payout using more lines. 

 

Payouts are based on left-to-right symbol repetitions for each line, starting from 3x 

symbol repetitions to 5x.  

 

The payout distribution is listed below for winning combinations of different symbols for 

each line. Each symbol is denoted by an alphabet ‚Äì which would be substituted by their 

respective symbols in the actual game. 

 
3xA ‚Äì 10 4xA - 20 5xA - 30 

3xB ‚Äì 20 4xB - 40 5xB - 60 

3xC ‚Äì 40 4xC - 80 5xC - 120 

3xD ‚Äì 50 4xD - 100 5xD - 150 

3xE ‚Äì 75 4xE - 150 5xE - 225 

3xF ‚Äì 150 4xF - 300 5xF - 450 

3xG ‚Äì 300 4xG - 600 5xG - 900 

 
 

Slots will consist of 5 reels containing 7 different symbols each with varying frequencies 

giving multiple winning combinations at different probabilities. The frequency 

distribution for each symbol in each reel is given below: 

 

S     R1 R2 R3 R4 R5 

A 4 4 7 6 7 

B 5 4 4 6 4 

C 4 6 2 3 3 

D 2 2 4 1 3 

E 4 2 2 2 1 

F 1 2 1 2 2 

G 1 1 1 1 1 

This gives us a distribution of 21 symbols for each reel.  



Page 16 of 29                                   
 

 

The total number of different combinations would now be 21^5 or 4,084,101 different 

combinations.Based on the reels distribution listed above, the probability of a winning 

combination would be 9.433165%  

 

Returns to users based on different winning combinations based on the reels 

distribution and payouts mentioned above would be around 93.08291%. 

 

100% of the profits generated would be distributed among holders of DBET House 

Credits as part of each session profit distributions.  As stated in 4.1 the 5% balance is 

reserved for a single lottery drawing. The game itself will create the experience of 

actually playing the slots in a casino and would be playable across multiple screen 

sizes. We believe that mobile support will go a long way to increase adoption and user 

retention. 

 

 

6.4 Craps 

 
 

Craps will be the second casino game on the Decent.bet platform.  The game will be 

offered with one table per player due to the user experience issues that would arise on 

a game with multiple players being required to push transactions into a smart contract.  

 

The craps game will be user-friendly and in-line with our vision to create a platform that 

is both transparent and provides a responsive user experience that will go a long way 

towards increasing adoption.  

 

Craps will also make use of state channels with pre-determined random numbers 

making use of blended seeds and their hashes. Users will always play against the 

house and will be able to choose between pass and don‚Äôt pass lines to start, before 

rolling their die.  

Once the die is rolled on the front-end, a random number is generated based on the 

turn and its respective blended seed. It then checks for the following conditions for a 

pass line bet;  



Page 17 of 29                                   
 

 

1. If the sum of the die is 7 or 11, the user wins the game. If the sum of the die is 2, 3 

or 12, the house wins the game. 

 

2. If the above conditions aren‚Äôt met, the previously retrieved sum is now set as the 

‚Äúpoint‚Äù. Now, the user and the house gets to roll repeatedly until either the point or a 7 

comes up. If the point comes up first, the user wins. If a 7 comes up first, the house 

wins. 

 

3. All user winnings are double of the amount that was bet.  

 

For don‚Äôt pass line bets, the conditions are swapped between the user and house.  

As with other Casino games on the platform, 100% of the profits generated would be 

distributed among holders of DBET House Credits as part of each session profit 

distributions. 

 
 

6.5 Other Games 

 
 

Over time, other casino games will be added on to the platform based on user 

demand in the form of smart contracts and state channels while making use of 

DBETs for all transactions. 



